        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#vertebrate_core"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Editor note: surface epithelium may contain non-epithelial cells, such as melanocytes, lymphocytes and dendritic cells, within the sheet of epithelial cells. Do we consider these part of the epithelium, or located-in it?</rdfs:comment>
