        <owl:annotatedTarget>The ciliary muscle is a ring of smooth muscle in the middle layer of the eye that controls the eye&apos;s accommodation for viewing objects at varying distances and regulates the flow of aqueous humour through Schlemm&apos;s canal. [WP,unvetted].</owl:annotatedTarget>
