        <obo:IAO_0000115>Muscle tissue is a contractile tissue made up of actin and myosin fibers[GO].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:RO_0002171 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003714"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>One of the four types of tissue in traditional classifications. Tissue that contains cells with contractile filaments that move past each other and change the size of the cell. Muscle tissue also is separated into three distinct categories.[AAO]</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
