        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="genid2100"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="genid2102"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A region of embryonic ectodermal cells that lie directly above the notochord. During neurulation, they change shape and produce an infolding of the neural plate (the neural fold) that then seals to form the neural tube[XAO]. The earliest recognizable dorsal ectodermal primordium of the central nervous system present near the end of gastrulation before infolding to form the neural keel; consists of a thickened pseudostratified epithelium[ZFA].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>The earliest recognizable dorsal ectodermal primordium of the central nervous system present near the end of gastrulation before infolding to form the neural keel; consists of a thickened pseudostratified epithelium. Kimmel et al, 1995.[TAO]</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000003>(...) at some stage of its development, every chordate exhibits five uniquely derived characters or synapomorphies of the group: (...) (4) a single, tubular nerve cord that is located dorsal to the notochord (...).[well established][VHOG]</obo:UBPROP_0000003>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>AAO:0011072</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>BTO:0001765</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
