            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The subdivision of the face that includes the eye (eyeball plus adnexa such as eyelids) and the orbit of the skull and associated parts of the face such as the eyebrows, if present.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>note the FMA class is more narrow though, and is more like eye + muscles + vasculature. The FMA also has FMA:72951 orbital part of eye</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>in HP covers eyelid, eyebrow.</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FMA:260119</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>content of orbital part of eye</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>eye region</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>orbital part of face</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>uberon</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>ocular and peri-ocular region</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>ocular region</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>orbital content</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>orbital part of eye</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>UBERON:0004088</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#pheno_slim"/>
        <rdfs:label>orbital region</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
