        <obo:IAO_0000115>A transparent homogeneous acellular layer found between the substantia propria and the endothelial layer of the cornea[MP].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>Acellular anatomical structure composed of collagen, Descemet&apos;s membrane is secreted as a basement membrane of the corneal endothelium. Located between the stroma and the corneal endothelium, it is approximately 0.15 micrometer thick at 6 months post-fertilization.[ZFIN]</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
