    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0005085 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0005085">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001048"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000924"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm[GO].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>consder adding placodal ectoderm as a distinct class? Also place placodal ectoderm as develops_from ectoderm; need to check taxon-appropriateness</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000008>With the exception of the adenohypophysis, homologues of the nonneurogenic placodes (e.g. placodes giving rise to the teeth, hair follicles and lens), appear to be lacking in invertebrate chordates.</obo:UBPROP_0000008>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>in GO, covers optic, otic, olfactory, mammary, hair, tooth, sebaceous - and also insect structures</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>AEO:0000218</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>uberon</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>epithelial placode</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>UBERON:0005085</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:label>ectodermal placode</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
